{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "We assessed the presence or absence of interactions within the dataset for each pair of scaffolds.",
    "We created a binary interaction profile matrix in which each cell (i, j) indicates whether scaffold i interacts with scaffold j (0 for no interaction, 1 otherwise).",
    "Each row is a binary vector describing the interaction partners for each scaffold.",
    "By using a binary vector instead of counting the number of interactions between each scaffold, the bias in the rules due to imbalance in the dataset was removed.",
    "This matrix also answers whether we can infer potential interaction partners for a molecule based on its scaffold."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}